    "Session 2: Understanding Psychological Distress Session two delves into the nature of psychological distress, including its causes, symptoms, and effects on daily life.",
    "Through interactive discussions and activities, participants are encouraged to identify their own experiences of distress.",
    "The session introduces basic principles of CBT as a tool for recognizing and challenging negative thought patterns contributing to distress.",
    "Session 8: Review and Forward Planning The final session reviews the key concepts and skills covered throughout the program.",
    "Participants reflect on their progress towards their personal goals and discuss their experiences of implementing the strategies learned."
